adviseScripts.text: Why do people always assume I enjoy spicy food?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Do I smell spicy or something?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: It's because eating spicy food is painful.
It's because you give off an irritated vibe.
Oh, my.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Ha ha, I suppose that's true. That is why I love spicy food so much.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I see. I didn't realize I gave off that vibe.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: But what does that have to do with liking spicy food, anyway?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Mihara and I experiment with the limits of spiciness.
Yuni is so loveable.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Why do you think that is?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Everything she does is just adorable.
Some people are just loveable. There's no reason behind it.
You're not wrong, and yet...
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: there are times when her whining gets on my nerves.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Not everything she does is so loveable. After all, nobody's perfect.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Hm. That is true.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Trying to find the reason is pointless.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Love can never truly be explained.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with Mihara about Yuni.
Commander, what do you think my type is?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Um... when it comes to boys, I mean.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Tall, good-looking, and a great personality.
Someone who can accommodate your... preferences.
Ha ha! You're right. That would be like a dream come true. But, I suppose everyone wants the same thing.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Actually, I've already met the man of my dreams.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: And, as a matter of fact, he's somewhere very close by.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Hm... Not necessarily.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: A man who can accommodate me would be nice, but that's far from being my ideal type.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I spend time with Mihara talking about our celebrity crushes.
I was out on a mission capturing a Rapture when a thought crossed my mind.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I realized that I have a natural talent for this sort of work.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Commander, what do you think I would be? If I wasn't a Nikke, of course.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: ... A shepherd?
... A bounty hunter?
A shepherd?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Hm... sounds kind of fun.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: But I think I'm better suited to dealing with humans, not animals.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Yes... I think that would suit me very well.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: It has some decent thrill to it as well.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: If I decide to do that later on, would you be interested in joining me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I listen to Mihara's detailed lecture on how to tie people up.
I always want to share the stuff I'm into with others.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: However, I always feel like there's so much distance between me and everyone else.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Is there any way I can get rid of that distance?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Take your time and use your powers of persuasion.
Use your experience to make them fall for you.
I suppose that is the right thing to do.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Some things just take time to get used to.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text:
I'll take my time. I'll go really slow.
I'll make them understand, bit by bit...
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Ha ha. It's an appealing proposition.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: However, I'm not entirely sure I can make that work every time.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Though, trying might be fun in its own way...
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I have a deep conversation with Mihara about her preferences.
The line between pain and pleasure is so, so thin.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text:
Sometimes you're being crushed by pain you can barely take,
and the next moment it crosses the line into intense pleasure.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Doesn't it make you curious, Commander?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Not one bit.
I'm curious, but it kind of scares me.
Hm... really?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I thought you'd at least be somewhat interested. I guess I was wrong.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Ha ha. New things are always a bit intimidating.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Don't be scared. We can take it one step at a time. I'll show you everything.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I watch a video of painful parkour fails with Mihara.
There are so many stores on the Royal Road.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: One of them is very, very secretive and mysterious.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Doesn't that make you curious?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Let's go right now.
... Not really.
Oh, my. Really?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Lovely. I hear they actually let you use their merchandise in the store.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Let's go have some fun. Okay?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Oh, my! You're not embarrassed, are you?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Hm... I didn't expect that. I thought you were a bit more adventurous.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Oh, well. It doesn't matter. I'll go there with Yuni later.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Mihara tells me more about the unique items that can be found on Royal Road.
Taking care of your body is important.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: If I want to keep enjoying my particular hobbies for a long time, I'll need to keep my body in tip-top shape.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Speaking of which, do you have any health tips you can share?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Consistent exercise and a good diet.
Stay away from stressful situations.
Commander, those things don't really apply to a Nikke...
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Wouldn't it be better to focus more on the mental side of things?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Yes! That's the most important thing.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Ha ha. I always thought that, as a Commander, you would always be stressed out by your work.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Perhaps I was wrong?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Just like I thought. You are exceptional.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I watch a video about mental health with Mihara.
These clothes I'm wearing...
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Are they a little... weird?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I think they're very nice.
Something a little more modest might be better...
Ha ha! Really? Okay, then.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: As long as the Commander likes them, I couldn't care less what other people think.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: But... this is modest! For me, at least...
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: At this rate, I'll have to walk around in a burlap sack...
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I spend time with Mihara looking at fashion magazines.
Yuni has been rather busy lately.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I haven't been able to see her that much.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Do you think there's something going on?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Have you ever considered that she may just need some rest?
I'm sure she is working on some new skills.
No way.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Yuni never stops, no matter what.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I'm worried. I really should go pay her a visit.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Oh, my. Just hearing that makes my body quiver.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: You're probably right. Yuni must be preparing a special surprise for me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I'll just have to wait and see what it is!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Listen to Mihara gush about Yuni.
Check out this new leather strap that I bought.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: What do you think? Get a good look at it, and make sure to feel it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Touch it.
Don't touch it.
Such a smooth texture, right? And sturdy as well.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Do you like it?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Hehe, don't be afraid.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I won't ask you to tie me up until you've gotten used to all of this.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Seems you're still a bit put off by all this.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: What a shame. Fine then, we'll find something else to play with.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Mihara helped broaden my horizons and shared some scandalous information.
I've used up all my scented candles so I'm going to buy some more.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Which scent should I buy?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I wanted to get something that you'd like.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Something sweet.
Something refreshing.
The one I used before had a sweet scent...
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Well, if that's what you want...
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I suppose I can buy the same thing again. I'll be using it on you, after all.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: That's exactly what I was thinking!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: That's good, I was really looking forward to trying out something new.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: We can have some fun using it together.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Mihara taught me all sorts of new things about candles.
Commander, do you know why I take such pleasure in salacious activities?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Because you like pain.
Because you want to be controlled by others.
Hehe, you're very perceptive at times.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Correct. Pain makes you realize you are alive.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: That's what I love so much about it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Huh? That's not true at all.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: It's the other way around. I enjoy controlling others.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with Mihara about her turn-ons and turn-offs.
Commander, if you had to choose between
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: something new and something familiar, which would you pick?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Something new.
Something familiar.
I see, so the same as me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I get a thrill from new experiences as well.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Once I get too familiar with something, it no longer stimulates me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Interesting...
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Personally, I enjoy new experiences.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: If I don't move on to something new, it quickly gets stale for me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Mihara and I concoct various ways to find stimulation.
Since the weather is so nice, I was thinking of going for a walk.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: What should I take with me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: A packed lunch.
A leash, maybe?
As long as you pack it for me, sure!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I'd love to go on a nice little picnic.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: It should be a nice change of pace.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Such a new experience... I'm tingling with anticipation!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I just wanted to walk around the Outpost.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: What exactly did you have in mind?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: You little pervert, hehe.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I went on a walk with Mihara.
Commander, between the mind and the body,
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: which do you think is more important?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Body.
Mind.
Hmm... really? I suppose that's because you're a human.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: If your body sustains any injuries, you don't recover so easily, so I understand why you would feel that way.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Personally, I think it's more frightening to suffer a mental collapse.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Me too.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: The mind is capable of inflicting far more pain than the body ever could.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Mihara and I have a discussion about the correlation between the body and mind.
I was considering getting some exercise.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: What type of exercise do you think would best suit me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Jump rope.
I thought Nikkes didn't have to exercise?
Yes... The pain of constantly jumping over a rope that is about to hit you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: The sting when it finally makes contact, and the fact that you brought this pain upon yourself...
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: It's perfect.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: You're right,
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: but I've had an urge recently to get my body in motion.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: If you don't have any recommendations, then I'll just have to figure it out myself.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Mihara and I talk about exercise.
Commander, have you ever had the urge to steal
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: something from someone else?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: No, I haven't.
Yes, I have.
I figured as much.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I knew you and I were different.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Well, I've stolen before.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: You're not pulling my leg, are you?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: It's nice to know that we have something in common,
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: even if it's rather unexpected.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I was so envious of someone else's life that I wanted to steal their very essence.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Perhaps that is how I came to have this ability.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I spend time talking with Mihara.
I have to be honest with you Commander, I've been keeping a secret from you this entire time.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Can you guess what it is?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I'll let you know if you get it right?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: But if you tell me, it'll no longer be a secret.
You know Syuene's weakness?
Very true. By definition, a secret is only a secret when no one else knows.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: The moment I tell you what it is, it will cease to be a secret.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: You're a tough nut to crack, Commander.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I think that's what I like about you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Let me see... correct, or incorrect?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: As soon as I tell you it's correct, it no longer becomes a secret.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Therefore I can't tell you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Mihara and I talk about secrets.
Commander, which do you think is more precious?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: The memories you've already accumulated, or the memories you'll create in the future?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: All the previous memories I've gathered.
The memories I'll create in the future.
Why?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: They've made me into the person I am today.
Hmm... my view differs slightly.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I feel I'm a much better person now than I was in the past.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Why?
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Because the person I am now will be the one making those new memories.
Precisely!
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I couldn't agree more.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: I've always preferred my current self to who I was in the past.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Therefore, it's a no-brainer that the experiences I'm having now are superior to those of the past.
adviseScripts.speaker: Mihara

adviseScripts.text: Mihara and I talk about the concept of memories.
